description:
The Architecture of Michelangelo
Viking Press | 1961 | ISBN: N/A | English | 286 pages | PDF | 43.6 MB

This monograph is the first in English in which all of Michelangelo's architecture is collected and analyzed; it draws upon the accomplishment of a century of scholarship in five countries, which has brought to light letters, documents, notes and drawings of and about the great Florentine, and has revealed his true stature as an architect and engineer
